Today’s Work Update (12-05-2026)

Today I worked on building an AI workflow using Langflow, where I created a basic Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system. During this process, I integrated ChromaDB as the vector database to store and retrieve embedded information efficiently, and used LiteLLM for handling model interactions.

I also configured a simple URL-based data ingestion pipeline, which allowed me to scrape and process web content directly into the workflow. The main components I used included a URL parser, prompt template, ChromaDB, and LiteLLM.

For testing, I used the MDH website as a practical example. I scraped relevant information from the site and tested the system with the question: “What does MDH stand for?” The workflow successfully retrieved the required information from the website and generated an accurate response.

Overall, today’s work helped me gain practical experience in:

* Langflow workflow building
* RAG system development
* ChromaDB integration
* LiteLLM configuration
* Web scraping and URL data ingestion
* Prompt structuring for AI responses

This was an important step in improving my understanding of AI-powered knowledge retrieval systems and real-world workflow automation.
